Sentencas: The oxygen stoichiometry, conductivity, and thermal expansion behavior of lanthanum strontium copper iron oxide (La0.7Sr0.3Cu0.2Fe0.8O3-delta) have been investigated because of its potential application as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: The oxygen non-stoichiometry and electrical conductivity of La0.7Sr0.3Cu0.2Fe0.8O3-δ

Sentencas: The relative oxygen non-stoichiometry of La0.7Sr0.3Cu0.2Fe0.8O3-delta as a function of pO(2) has been obtained by solid-state coulometric titration at 800 <= T <= 1000 degrees C and at 10(-13) <= pO(2) <= 0.5 atm.
Titulo: The oxygen non-stoichiometry and electrical conductivity of La0.7Sr0.3Cu0.2Fe0.8O3-δ

Sentencas: Two discontinuities in the pO(2) dependence of the stoichiometry and unexpected hysteresis effects were observed at the temperatures measured.
Titulo: The oxygen non-stoichiometry and electrical conductivity of La0.7Sr0.3Cu0.2Fe0.8O3-δ

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity behavior as a function of pO(2) and temperature was determined and related to the oxygen non-stoichiometry.
Titulo: The oxygen non-stoichiometry and electrical conductivity of La0.7Sr0.3Cu0.2Fe0.8O3-δ
